qas.question: What pulls the aircraft to one of the airbridges?
What keeps the electricity running in the plane when it stands at the terminal?
What can give the ground crew more clearance after the aircraft lands?
How long should it take for an aircraft to be off the airport and in the air?
What do engines generate when planes are standing at the terminal?
Where do the ground crew disembark from?

plausible_answers.text: the awkwardly shaped, or late luggage

qas.question: What does the ground crew use the skybridge to bring in after its pushed on one of the tractor dollies?
What pulls an airbridge to the aircraft?
When should the ground crew be done removing luggage?

context: Many ground crew at the airport work at the aircraft. A <a0_0><b8_0>tow tractor<b8_0/><a0_0/> pulls the aircraft to one of the airbridges, The <a1_0>ground power unit<a1_0/> is plugged in. It keeps the electricity running in the plane when it stands at the terminal. The engines are not working, therefore they do not generate <b5_0>the electricity<b5_0/>, as they do in flight. The passengers disembark using <b6_0>the <a2_0>airbridge<b6_0/><a2_0/>. <a3_0>Mobile stairs<a3_0/> can give the ground crew more access to the aircraft's cabin. There is a cleaning service to clean the aircraft after the aircraft lands. Flight catering provides the food and drinks on flights. A toilet waste truck removes the human waste from the tank which holds the waste from the toilets in the aircraft. A water truck fills the water tanks of the aircraft. A fuel transfer vehicle transfers aviation fuel from fuel tanks underground, to the aircraft tanks. A tractor and its dollies bring in luggage from the terminal to the aircraft. They also carry luggage to the terminal if the aircraft has landed, and is being unloaded. Hi-loaders lift the heavy luggage containers to the gate of the cargo hold. The ground crew push the luggage containers into the hold. If it has landed, they rise, the ground crew push the luggage container on the hi-loader, which carries it down. The luggage container is then pushed on one of the tractors dollies. The conveyor, which is a conveyor belt on a truck, brings in <b7_0>the awkwardly shaped, or late luggage<b7_0/>. The airbridge is used again by the new passengers to embark the aircraft. The tow tractor pushes the aircraft away from the terminal to a taxi area. The aircraft should be off of the airport and in the air <b9_0>in <a4_0>90 minutes<b9_0/><a4_0/>. The airport charges the airline for the time the aircraft spends at the airport.
